CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Nucleus {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:Q2WG80}.
CC   -!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: In the late gastrula stage, expression appears in
CC       the dorsal presomitic mesoderm and in the first three pairs of nascent
CC       somites. Expressed strongly in forming somites and then expression is
CC       rapidly down-regulated except in the first somite pair where expression
CC       is maintained for a longer period. Also expressed in the presumptive
CC       notochord and in the tail bud at the 48 hour larval stage. Expression
CC       disappears by the 72 hour stage. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:16211387}.
CC   -!- DOMAIN: The ripply homology domain is required for transcriptional
CC       repression. {ECO:0000250}.
CC   -!- DOMAIN: The WRPW motif is required for binding to TLE/GROUCHO proteins.
